Step 1: Identify the required figures.
• Main Business Revenue (from the income statement) = 3,397,619.40  
• Total Assets on the beginning date (from the balance sheet) = 13,000,000.00  
• Total Assets on the ending date (from the balance sheet) = 14,799,664.61  

Step 2: Calculate the average of the total assets.
 Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
 = (13,000,000.00 + 14,799,664.61) / 2  
 = 27,799,664.61 / 2  
 = 13,899,832.305  

Step 3: Compute the Total Asset Turnover Ratio.
 Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Main Business Revenue / Average Total Assets  
 = 3,397,619.40 / 13,899,832.305  
 ≈ 0.24445

Rounding to two decimal places gives approximately 0.24.

Thus, the solution is:
